==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Persian]] words {{FAchar|&#1662;&#1575;&#1610;&#1580;&#1575;&#1605;&#1607;}} ''pɑ jɑma'' meaning ''leg garment'' via [[Urdu]]/[[Hindi]] word ''pajama''.

===Noun===
'''pajamas''' ''plural''

Wrong definition: #[[Clothes]] for wearing to bed and sleeping in, usually consisting of a loose-fitting shirt and pants.

Correct Definition:
A leg garment loose or tight, holds to the wasteline by strings. A shirt that accompanies a pajama is called "Kurta".

